ms of the Lee Kuan Yew School of Public Policy, National University of Singapore; V. Anatha-Nageswaran, Chief Investment Officer for Asia-Pacific at Bank Julius Baer; Michael Lim Mah Hui, a former banker, author and professor and currently a Senior Fellow in the Asian Public Intellectuals Program of the Nippon Foundation; Pradumna B. Rana, Senior Fellow at the Nanyang Technological University in Singapore and formerly a Senior Director at the Asian Development Bank; and Lim Chin, a Professor of Economics at the Business School of the National University of Singapore. The commentaries were also circulated on the Internet. In addition, we have included an article, “What ASEAN Must Do to Cope with the Crisis”, by Sanchita Basu Das of the ASEAN Studies Centre and a Visiting Research Fellow at the Institute of Southeast Asian Studies. We have done so with the kind permission of the Business Times, where the article first appeared.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aGlobal Financial Crisis, 2008-2009. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / International Relations / Trade & Tariffs.2bisacsh1 aASEAN Studies Centre, , eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aAdams, Charles, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAnantha-Nageswaran, V., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChin, Lim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDas, Sanchita Basu, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHui, Michael Lim Mah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKawai, Masahiro, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRana, Pradumna B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSeverino, Rodolfo C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary